free.freechess
Class Style12Struct

java.lang.Object
  free.util.Struct
      free.freechess.Style12Struct

public class Style12Struct
extends Struct

A structure holding parsed information from a style12 line. See http://www.freechess.org/WWWhelp/style12.html or the "help style12" helpfile on freechess.org for information about the format.

Style12Struct

public Style12Struct(java.lang.String boardLexigraphic,
                     java.lang.String currentPlayer,
                     int doublePawnPushFile,
                     boolean canWhiteCastleKingside,
                     boolean canWhiteCastleQueenside,
                     boolean canBlackCastleKingside,
                     boolean canBlackCastleQueenside,
                     int pliesSinceIrreversible,
                     int gameNumber,
                     java.lang.String whiteName,
                     java.lang.String blackName,
                     int gameType,
                     boolean isPlayedGame,
                     boolean isMyTurn,
                     int initTime,
                     int increment,
                     int whiteMaterialStrength,
                     int blackMaterialStrength,
                     int whiteTime,
                     int blackTime,
                     int nextMoveNumber,
                     java.lang.String moveVerbose,
                     java.lang.String moveSAN,
                     int moveTime,
                     boolean isBoardFlipped,
                     boolean isClockRunning,
                     int lag)
Creates a new Style12Struct with the specified arguments. You would usually want to use the parseStyle12Line method and not this constructor to obtain Style12Struct objects.

Parameters:
boardLexigraphic - The current board, in lexigraphic format.
currentPlayer - The player to move, either "B" or "W".
doublePawnPushFile - The file of the double pawn push on the last move, or -1 if the last move wasn't a double pawn push.
canWhiteCastleKingside - Can white castle kingside?
canWhiteCastleQueenside - Can white castle queenside?
canBlackCastleKingside - Can black castle kingside?
canBlackCastleQueenside - Can black castle queenside?
pliesSinceIrreversible - The number of half moves made since the last irreversible move (0 if the last move is irreversible).
gameNumber - The game number.
whiteName - The white player's nickname.
blackName - The black player's nickname.
gameType - The code for the type of the game. Possible values are MY_GAME, OBSERVED_GAME and ISOLATED_BOARD.
isPlayedGame - true if the game is played,
isMyTurn - Is it my turn or the opponent's? Only relevant if gameType is MY_GAME and it's a played game. false if it's an examined game.
initTime - Initial time (in seconds) of the match.
increment - Increment (in seconds) of the match.
whiteMaterialStrength - White's material strength.
blackMaterialStrength - Black's material strength.
whiteTime - White's remaining time, in milliseconds.
blackTime - Black's remaining time, in milliseconds.
nextMoveNumber - The number of the move about to be made (standard chess numbering -- White's and Black's first moves are both 1, etc.)
moveVerbose - A verbose representation of the last move, null if none.
movePretty - A SAN (Standard Algebraic Notation) representation of the last move, null if none.
moveTime - The amount of time taken to make the last move, in milliseconds.
isBoardFlipped - true if the board should be flipped (black at bottom), false otherwise.
isClockRunning - true if the clock of the player to move is running.
lag - The lag incurred when making the move, in milliseconds.
